<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 06 at 2:30AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow at times through the early afternoon...
Snow is forecast to develop from southwest to northeast across
eastern portions of Southwest Montana this morning. Overall, 1 to
2 inches of snow is likely below pass level. Be prepared for
locally slick roads and reduced visibility at times due to snow.
Snow will diminish in the early afternoon at lower elevations.</description>
